# ============================================================================
# Kiyo Food – Frontend Environment Variables (Vite)
# ============================================================================
#
# These variables are read by the browser bundle at build time (Vite exposes
# only variables prefixed with VITE_). Set them in:
#
#   * Vercel  → Project → Settings → Environment Variables (Production +
#               Preview + Development, as needed)
#   * Local   → copy this file to `.env.local` (gitignored) and fill values
#
# After any change here, trigger a Vercel redeploy so the bundle is rebuilt.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Required – Supabase (database, auth, storage, realtime)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-public-anon-key

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional – public site config (no secrets!)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Public, deployment-time URLs used by SEO/structured data and the OAuth
# callback target. Override these per-environment so the same bundle can run
# against localhost, preview, and production without code changes.
VITE_SITE_URL=https://kiyo-food.store
VITE_PUBLIC_APP_NAME=Kiyo Food

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional – Maps (Leaflet + OpenStreetMap is the default; no key needed)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The bundled map stack is Leaflet + OpenStreetMap (via the public
# Nominatim tile servers). No API key is required for it.
#
# If you ever switch to Google Maps Platform (charged per request), you
# would add a restricted public key here:
#   VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=AIza...
# …and update src/components/DeliveryMap.tsx + TrackingMap.tsx accordingly.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Reserved for future integrations
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# These are intentionally not consumed yet by the frontend; documented here
# so the production launch checklist is complete and so anyone spinning up
# a fresh environment knows what the platform expects.
#
# VITE_SENTRY_DSN=                 # client-side error tracking
# VITE_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID=G-XXXXXX  # analytics (when you set up GA4)
